A member of the Confluence team once gave me the advice to use relative URLs whenever possible, because the instance Base URLs are often not set or set incorrectly. 

I was just running the Team Calendars plugin and noticed that the link telling me to renew my license was incorrect. It turned out an AMPS issue caused my Base URL to be set improperly. But this AMPS issue would not have mattered if the link were instead relative. 

One example in the code:
{{new StringBuilder(settingsManager.getGlobalSettings().getBaseUrl()).append(licenseAccessor.getLicenseManagerUrl()).toString()}}
but instead it would be nice if this were
{{new StringBuilder(getContextPath()).append(licenseAccessor.getLicenseManagerUrl()).toString()}}.
I'm not sure how to best get the context path in all circumstances, however, though I know that in velocity you can use {{$req.contextPath}}.

